<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,310,717,743]" box="[189,310,717,743]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,717,743]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,717,743]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,1399,764,1001]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Shell very small to relatively large (adult diameter ± 1.3–2.0 mm), spire slightly sunken to slightly elevated; umbilicus moderate to very wide; whorls strongly rounded, periphery at mid-whorl. Protoconch smooth or with low, weakly undulant axial sculpture. Teleoconch with close-set axial riblets; riblets compound, composed of several periostracal lamellae; intervals between riblets with several finer intermediary axial threads; spiral sculpture weak, at most comprising extremely fine, close-set spiral threads. Aperture lunate to broadly lunate, variously furnished with parietal and palatal dentition in the form of denticles and/or in-running lamellae/ridges.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,324,1033,1059]" box="[189,324,1033,1059]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1033,1059]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1033,1059]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[189,1399,1079,1140]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[377,452,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">phiala</emphasis>
: a saucer or bowl, and 
<emphasis box="[736,803,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">donta</emphasis>
: a contraction of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melvill &amp; Ponsonby" authorityYear="1908" box="[1016,1134,1079,1105]" class="Gastropoda" family="Endodontidae" genus="Afrodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1134,1079,1105]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Afrodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; with reference to the wide, shallow umbilicus. Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
