<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[189,1399,316,533]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName authority="Herbert, 2020" authorityName="Herbert" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,334,316,342]" class="Gastropoda" family="Charopidae" genus="Phialodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,334,316,342]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Phialodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[343,452,317,343]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is proposed for a group of species which share a smooth or weakly sculptured protoconch and a relatively coarse teleoconch sculpture of compound axial riblets with multiple fine intermediary axial threads. The genus ranges widely, from the Agulhas region, W. 
<collectingRegion box="[1140,1200,392,418]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Cape</collectingRegion>
to the KwaZulu- Natal 
<collectingRegion box="[260,375,430,456]" country="Zimbabwe" name="Midlands" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Midlands</collectingRegion>
. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Herbert, 2020" authorityName="Herbert" authorityYear="2020" box="[418,576,430,456]" class="Gastropoda" family="Charopidae" genus="Costulodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[418,576,430,456]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Costulodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,691,431,457]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the protoconch has distinct radial riblets and the teleoconch sculpture is generally somewhat finer. Members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melvill &amp; Ponsonby" authorityYear="1908" box="[791,909,468,494]" class="Gastropoda" family="Endodontidae" genus="Afrodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[791,909,468,494]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Afrodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a somewhat similar protoconch, but they possess a silky teleoconch sculpture comprised of simple axial riblets of alternating strength.
</paragraph>
